                    <h1>SPICY Harissa Creamy Rigatoni</h1>
                    <p class="tag">BY JEREMY</p>

                    <img src="/img/dinner/vol4/2.svg" class="img2" alt="">

                    <div class="content">
                        <div class="sub-section-1">
                            <h6>Ingredients:</h6>


                            <ul>
                                <li>1/2 cup rigatoni</li>
                                <li>1/2 cup water</li>
                                <li>1/4 cup tomato paste</li>
                                <li>2 tbsp heavy cream or half-and-half</li>
                                <li>1/2 tsp New York Shuk Rosey Harissa Spice</li>
                                <li>1 tbsp sun-dried tomatoes, finely chopped</li>
                                <li>1 tbsp grated parmesan cheese, plus extra for garnish</li>
                                <li>1/4 tsp garlic powder</li>
                                <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
                                <li>Fresh basil leaves, thinly sliced</li>
                                <li>Drizzle of high-quality olive oil for finishing</li>
                            </ul>

                        </div>
                        <div class="sub-section-2">
                            <h6>Instruction:</h6>
                            <div class="text">



                                <h4>1. THE PASTA</h4>
                                <p>Place the rigatoni and water in a large microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for
                                    4-5 minutes, stirring halfway, until pasta is al dente and most of the water is
                                    absorbed.</p>

                                <h4>2. SAUCE IT UP</h4>
                                <p>Add tomato paste, cream, Rosey Harissa Spice, sun-dried tomatoes, parmesan, garlic
                                    powder, salt, and pepper. Stir well to combine all ingredients.</p>

                                <h4>3. MICROWAVE</h4>
                                <p>Microwave on high for 1-2 minutes until the sauce is creamy, and the flavors are
                                    melded. The garlic powder and sun-dried tomatoes will add depth and richness to the
                                    sauce.</p>

                                <h4>4. KILL</h4>
                                <p>Let sit for a minute to thicken. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle extra parmesan, and
                                    garnish with fresh basil before serving.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

